 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Holy Sonnet 1</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sonnet">
     <l n="1" met="+-+---++-+">Thou hast made me, and shall thy work decay?</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+-+-+-+-+">Repair me now, for now mine end doth haste;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+-+-+++-+">I run to death, and death meets me as fast,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+-+--++-+">And all my pleasures are like yesterday.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+++-+++-+|-+-+-+++-+">I dare not move my dim eyes any way,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+-+-+-+-+">Despair behind and death before doth cast</l>
     <l n="7" met="++---+-+-+">Such terror, and my feeble flesh doth waste</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+-+-+-+-+">By sin in it, which it towards hell doth weigh.</l>
     <l n="9" met="+-+--+-+-+">Only thou art above, and when towards thee</l>
     <l n="10" met="-++--+-+-+">By thy leave I can look, I rise again;</l>
     <l n="11" met="--++-+-+-+|--++-+++-+">But our old subtle foe so tempteth me</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+++-+---+">That not one hour myself I can sustain.</l>
     <l n="13" met="++-+---+-+">Thy grace may wing me to prevent his art,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+-+--+-+-+">And thou like adamant draw mine iron heart.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
